<!--
    ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
    ║  cpp_dbc CLASS HIERARCHY — LAYOUT SPECIFICATION FOR LLMs               ║
    ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║  LAYOUT TYPE: Flat matrix (no arrows, no lines of any kind).           ║
    ║  Inheritance is implied by position: same Y = same family,             ║
    ║  leftmost sub-column = most abstract.                                  ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║  BOX SIZE: All boxes are 250 × 50 (uniform).                           ║
    ║  SUB-COLUMN GAP: 290px (uniform across all zones).                     ║
    ║  INTER-ZONE GAP: 430px (between right edge of zone N and left edge     ║
    ║                   of zone N+1).                                        ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║  COLORS (by abstraction level):                                        ║
    ║    #dae8fc / #6c8ebf  = Root Abstract (blue)                           ║
    ║    #d5e8d4 / #82b366  = Family Abstract (green)                        ║
    ║    #fff2cc / #d6b656  = Concrete final (yellow)                        ║
    ║    #e1d5e7 / #9673a6  = Pool / Pooled infrastructure (purple)          ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║  ── X-AXIS: ZONES BY CLASS ROLE ──────────────────────────────────────  ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║  Each zone has sub-columns: Blue | Green | Yellow-1 | Yellow-2.        ║
    ║  Sub-column gap = 290px (uniform). Inter-zone gap = 430px.             ║
    ║  Not all zones have all sub-columns (marked with —).                   ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║  Zone          Blue    Green   Yel-1   Yel-2                           ║
    ║  ─────────────────────────────────────────────                          ║
    ║  Driver       -1470   -1180    -890    -600                             ║
    ║  Connection      80     370     660     950                             ║
    ║  ResultSet     1630    1920    2210    2500                             ║
    ║  PrepStmt         —    3180    3470    3760                             ║
    ║  Blob          4440       —    4730    5020                             ║
    ║  InputStream   5700       —    5990    6280                             ║
    ║  Doc-specific  6960       —    7250       —   (Collection)              ║
    ║                7540       —    7830       —   (Data)                    ║
    ║  Pool          8510    8800    9090    9380   (purple, not yellow)      ║
    ║  Pooled       10060   10350   10640   10930   (purple base, yellow)    ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║  ── Y-AXIS: ROWS BY DATABASE FAMILY ─────────────────────────────────  ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║  Row spacing ≈ 76.75px.                                                ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║  Y        Family       Concrete driver                                 ║
    ║  ──────────────────────────────────────                                 ║
    ║   12      Columnar     ScyllaDB                                        ║
    ║   88.75   Document     MongoDB                                         ║
    ║  165      KV           Redis                                           ║
    ║  240      Relational   row 1 (MySQL + PostgreSQL or SQLite)             ║
    ║  320      Relational   row 2 (SQLite + Firebird or PostgreSQL)          ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║  Root abstract classes always sit at y=12 in their zone's              ║
    ║  leftmost sub-column.                                                  ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║  ── 2×2 GRID FOR RELATIONAL CONCRETE CLASSES ────────────────────────  ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║  The 4 relational implementations use a 2×2 grid.                      ║
    ║  Dominant pattern (Driver, ResultSet, PrepStmt, Blob, InputStream):    ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║           col1           col2                                           ║
    ║  row1:   MySQL          PostgreSQL                                     ║
    ║  row2:   SQLite         Firebird                                       ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║  Exception — Connection zone uses a different grouping:                ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║           col1           col2                                           ║
    ║  row1:   MySQL          SQLite                                         ║
    ║  row2:   PostgreSQL     Firebird                                       ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║  ── POOL ZONE 2×2 GRID ──────────────────────────────────────────────  ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║  Pool families and Pooled connections use 2×2 grids:                   ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║  Pool families (x=9090/9380):                                          ║
    ║           col1              col2                                        ║
    ║  row1:   Relational(9090)   KV(9380)            y=12                   ║
    ║  row2:   Document(9090)     Columnar(9380)      y=88.75                ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║  Pooled connections (x=10640/10930):                                   ║
    ║           col1              col2                                        ║
    ║  row1:   Relational(10640)  Columnar(10930)     y=12                   ║
    ║  row2:   KV(10640)          Document(10930)     y=88.75                ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║  ── ADDING A NEW DRIVER ─────────────────────────────────────────────  ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ║  1. Determine the family (Relational, KV, Document, Columnar).         ║
    ║  2. Use the Y row assigned to that family.                             ║
    ║     - For single-impl families (KV, Document, Columnar): if a second   ║
    ║       driver is added, place it at the next Y increment (+76.75).      ║
    ║     - For Relational: extend the 2×2 grid to 3×2 or 2×3 as needed.    ║
    ║  3. Place each class in its corresponding zone's Yellow sub-column.    ║
    ║  4. Match the box style: fillColor=#fff2cc, strokeColor=#d6b656,       ║
    ║     250×50, fontSize=11 (or 10 for long names).                        ║
    ║                                                                        ║
    ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
-->
